cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extensions of finite automata and their properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the string separation problem for vector automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the recognition of languages by different types of automata. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of matrices in defining automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the computational power of different types of automata.
